beh: the behavioural data of the experiment saved in a csv text file
log: timing log files with timestamps of when events happened in the experiment.
settings: The settings as defined in the config file that were used in that experimental session
dotx_xy: The x,y coordinates of every dot on every frame of every trial per block. Stored as a Python pickle file (and a pandas dataframe inside). Can be read out with rdm_checkPositions.py
timing: Contains csv files with measured accuracy of frame flips.
